def create_ltm_profile(db, device_id, profile_type, profile_part, profile_name):
    """Construct create ltm profile command from the configuration
    """
    db_profile_data = Profiles.objects.get(type=profile_type, name=profile_name, device_id=device_id)
    # default_from_value = lambda config_data: re.search('defaults-from (.*?)\\n',config_data)
    fetch_last_value = lambda value: value.split('/')[-1]
    if profile_type == 'http':
        profile_cmd = 'create ltm profile ' + 'http /' + profile_part + '/' + profile_name
        matches = re.search('defaults-from (.*?)\\n', db_profile_data['configData'])
        if matches:
            profile_cmd += ' defaults-from ' + fetch_last_value(matches.group(1).strip('\n'))
        return profile_cmd
    elif profile_type in ('client-ssl', 'server-ssl'):
        chain_cmd = 'chain ' + fetch_last_value(db_profile_data['parameter']['chain']) if \
            'chain' in db_profile_data['parameter'] else ''
        chain_cert = ' cert ' + fetch_last_value(db_profile_data['parameter']['cert']) if \
            'cert' in db_profile_data['parameter'] else ''
        chain_key = 'key ' + fetch_last_value(db_profile_data['parameter']['key']) if \
            'key' in db_profile_data['parameter'] else ''
        profile_cmd = 'create ltm profile ' + profile_type + ' /' + profile_part + '/' + profile_name + chain_cert + ' ' + \
                      chain_key + ' ' + \
                      chain_cmd
        matches = re.search('defaults-from (.*?)\\n', db_profile_data['configData'])
        if matches:
            profile_cmd += ' defaults-from ' + fetch_last_value(matches.group(1).strip('\n'))
        return profile_cmd
    else:
        profile_cmd = 'create ltm profile ' + profile_type + ' /' + profile_part + '/' + profile_name
        matches = re.search('defaults-from (.*?)\\n', db_profile_data['configData'])
        if matches:
            profile_cmd += ' defaults-from ' + fetch_last_value(
                matches.group(1).strip('\n'))
        return profile_cmd


def create_ltm_persistence(device_id, persistence_type, persist_part, persistence_name):
    """Construct create ltm persistence command from the configuration
    """
    persist_type_props = {
        'cookie': ['cookie-name', 'always-send', 'method', 'override-connection-limit', 'expiration',
                   'defaults-from', 'app-service'],
        'dest-addr': ['match-across-services', 'match-across-pools', 'match-across-virtuals',
                      'mirror,mask,override-connection-limit', 'timeout', 'defaults-from'],
        'source-addr': ['match-across-services', 'match-across-pools', 'match-across-virtuals', 'mask',
                        'override-connection-limit', 'timeout', 'defaults-from'],
        'sip': ['match-across-services', 'match-across-pools', 'match-across-virtuals', 'mirror',
                'override-connection-limit', 'timeout', 'sip-info', 'defaults-from'],
        'ssl': ['match-across-services', 'match-across-pools', 'match-across-virtuals', 'mirror',
                'override-connection-limit', 'timeout', 'defaults-from']}
    config_data_obj = Profiles.objects.filter(device=device_id, code__in=['lpr', 'ltmpersistence'],
                                              partition_name='Common', name=persistence_name,
                                              type__in=['Persistence_Fallback', 'Persistence'])
    # config_data = db.me_adc.find_one(
    #     {'code': {'$in': ['ltmpersistence', 'lpr']}, 'type': {'$in': ['Persistence_Fallback', 'Persistence']}, 'name': persistence_name,
    #      'partition': 'Common',
    #      'deviceId': device_id}, {"configData": 1})

    persist_cmd = ''
    for properties in persist_type_props[persistence_type]:
        regex_cmd = 'mask \d*.\d*.\d*.\d*\\n | mask (.*?)\\n' if properties == 'mask' else '%s (.*?)\\n' % properties
        matches = re.search(regex_cmd, config_data_obj[0].config_data)
        if matches:
            persist_cmd += ' ' + properties + ' ' + matches.group(1).strip('\n').split('/')[-1]
    if persist_cmd:
        return 'create ltm persistence ' + persistence_type + ' /' + persist_part + '/' + persistence_name + persist_cmd
    else:
        raise Exception('Empty data in the db for selected persistence' + persistence_name)


def create_ltm_rule(device_id, device_version, irule_name):
    """Construct create ltm rule command from the configuration
    """
    time_stamp = str(datetime.datetime.now()).replace('-', '_').replace(':', '_').replace(' ', '_').split('.')[0]
    fileName = "delete_vip_temp_rule_" + time_stamp
    iruleConfig = Rules.objects.filter(device=device_id, name=irule_name)
    # iruleConfig = db.me_adc.find_one({"code": "lr", "deviceId": device_id, "name": irule_name}, {"configData": 1}).get(
    #     "configData")
    if iruleConfig:
        irule_config_string = str(iruleConfig[0].config_data)
        temp_irule_bash = "echo -e $" + repr(irule_config_string) + ' >/var/tmp/' + fileName

        if device_version == "v10":
            irule_merge_cmd = ['run util bash -c \"b merge /var/tmp/' + fileName + '\"']
        else:
            irule_merge_cmd = ['load sys config file /var/tmp/' + fileName + ' verify',
                               'load sys config file /var/tmp/' + fileName + ' merge']

    else:
        raise Exception("iRule config data missing in database. iRule Name: " + irule_name + " Device Id: " + device_id)

    return temp_irule_bash, irule_merge_cmd


def create_ltm_monitor(device_id, monitor_type, partition, monitor):
    """Construct create ltm monitor command from the configuration
    """
    monitor_param = ""
    http = ["interval", "timeout", "send", "recv", "recv-disable", "username", "password", "reverse", "destination"]
    https = ["interval", "timeout", "send", "recv", "recv-disable", "username", "password", "cipherlist", "reverse",
             "destination", "cert", "key"]
    tcp = ["interval", "timeout", "transparent", "destination"]
    config_data_obj = LtmMonitors.objects.filter(device=device_id, name=monitor, type=monitor_type)
    monitor_mapping_dict = {"http": http, "https": https, "tcp": tcp}
    if config_data_obj:
        for monitor_parameters in monitor_mapping_dict.get(monitor_type, []):
            match = re.search(monitor_parameters + "\s+(.*?)\\n",
                              config_data_obj[
                                  0].config_data)  # Regex to get the monitor parameter values in the monitor config data
            if match:
                monitor_param += monitor_parameters + " " + match.group(1) + " "
    else:
        raise Exception("Monitor config missing in the database. Monitor Name: " + monitor + " Device Id: " + device_id)

    return "create ltm monitor " + monitor_type + " /" + partition + "/" + monitor + " { " + monitor_param + " }"


def get_pool_member_command(device_id, device_version, pool):
    """Construct pool member command
    """
    member_cmd = ''
    default_state = 'down' if device_version == 'v10' else 'user-down'
    state_map = {'v10': {'enabled': 'up', 'disabled': 'down'},
                 'v11': {'enabled': 'user-up', 'disabled': 'user-down'},
                 'v12': {'enabled': 'user-up', 'disabled': 'user-down'},
                 'v13': {'enabled': 'user-up', 'disabled': 'user-down'}}
    fields_to_fetch = {'ip': 1, 'port': 1, 'ratio': 1, 'monitors': 1, 'priority': 1, 'state': 1}
    for lpm_id in pool.pool_members:
        member = LtmPoolMembers.objects.filter(_id=lpm_id.id)
        # member = db.me_adc.find_one({'_id': lpm_id, 'code': 'lpm'}, fields_to_fetch)
        ratio = (' ratio ' + member[0].ratio) if pool['lbmode'] == 'ratio-member' else ''
        priority = (' priority-group ' + member[0].priority) if (
                pool.priority and member[0].priority) else ''
        state = ' state ' + state_map[device_version].get('enabled' if member[0].state else 'disabled')
        member_cmd += ' ' + member[0].ip + ':' + str(member[0].port) + ' {' + priority + ratio + state + ' }'

    return (' members add {' + member_cmd + ' }') if member_cmd else ''


def create_ltm_pool(device_id, device_version, vip_pool_name):
    """Construct create ltm pool command from the configuration
    """
    remove_partition = lambda x: x.split('/')[-1]
    fields_to_fetch = {'lbmode': 1, 'lpm': 1, 'serviceDown': 1, 'monitorAll': 1, 'priority': 1, 'partition': 1}
    # pool = db.me_adc.find_one({'deviceId': device_id, 'code': 'lp', 'name': vip_pool_name}, fields_to_fetch)
    pool = LtmPools.objects.filter(device=device_id, name=vip_pool_name)[0]
    lb_mode_cmd = (' load-balancing-mode ' + pool.lbmode) if pool.lbmode else ''
    service_down_cmd = (' service-down-action ' + pool.service_down.lower()) if pool.service_down else ''
    monitor_list = list(filter(None, pool.monitor_names))
    monitor_cmd = (' monitor ' + ' and '.join(monitor_list)) if monitor_list else ''
    member_cmd = get_pool_member_command(device_id, device_version, pool) if pool.pool_members else ''
    create_pool = 'create ltm pool {name}{lbmode}{members}{monitors}{service_down}'.format(
        name='/' + pool.partition_name + '/' + vip_pool_name, lbmode=lb_mode_cmd, members=member_cmd,
        monitors=monitor_cmd, service_down=service_down_cmd)
    return create_pool

    # snatpool_rec = db.me_adc.find_one({'deviceId': device_id, 'code': 'ls', 'name': snatpool_name,'partition':partition}, {'ip': 1})

        ip_list = snatpool_rec[0].ip.strip().replace(',', ' ')

    return snatpool_cmd + snatpool_members


def get_profile_command(vip, device_id):
    """Create profile section of create ltm virtual command
    command is restructured in a way that all profiles will come first,
    then tcp-wan-optimized { context clientside }  tcp-lan-optimized { context serverside }
    """
    tcp_profiles = ''
    profiles = ''
    vip_profiles = vip.profile_names
    client_profiles = []
    server_profiles = []
    for prof in vip_profiles:
        client_profiles.extend(
            Profiles.objects.filter(device=device_id, name=prof.split('/')[-1], partition_name=prof.split('/')[-2],
                                    type='client-ssl'))
        server_profiles.extend(
            Profiles.objects.filter(device=device_id, name=prof.split('/')[-1], partition_name=prof.split('/')[-2],
                                    type='server-ssl'))
    del_profiles = []
    for client_profile in client_profiles:
        # client_profile = client_profile.split('/')[-1]
        if client_profile.name and get_profile_type(device_id, client_profile.name) not in ('client-ssl', 'server-ssl'):
            tcp_profiles += ' ' + client_profile.name + ' { context clientside }'
            del_profiles.append(client_profile.name)
    for server_profile in server_profiles:
        # server_profile = server_profile.split('/')[-1]
        if server_profile.name and get_profile_type(device_id, server_profile.name) not in ('client-ssl', 'server-ssl'):
            tcp_profiles += ' ' + server_profile.name + ' { context serverside }'
            del_profiles.append(server_profile.name)
    for prof in vip_profiles:
        profile = prof.split('/')[-1]
        profile_type = get_profile_type(device_id, profile)
        if profile_type and profile not in del_profiles:
            profiles += ' ' + profile + ' '
    if tcp_profiles.strip():
        tcp_profiles = ' profiles add { ' + tcp_profiles.strip() + ' }'
    if profiles:
        return ' profiles add {' + profiles + '}' + tcp_profiles
    else:
        return ''

def get_snatpool_name(config_data):
    """Return snatpool name if present in the config data
    """
    snatpool_name = ''
    # Extract snatpool config part
    match = re.search(r'source-address-translation.*pool.*type', config_data.replace('\n', '').replace('{ }', ''))
    if match:
        # Extract snatpool name part
        pool_name_part = re.search(r'pool\s[^\s]*', match.group(0))
        if pool_name_part:
            snatpool_name = pool_name_part.group(0).split()[-1]  # Extract snatpool name
            # snatpool_name = snatpool_name.split('/')[-1]    #Remove partition
    return snatpool_name

def is_bash_shell(device_name, device_ip, device_status):
    """Check device launched in bash mode or not
    """
    if device_status == 'Managed':
        username, password = Decrypt.getpassword(device_name)
        ssh_connection = paramiko.SSHClient()
        ssh_connection.set_missing_host_key_policy(paramiko.AutoAddPolicy())
        ssh_connection.connect(device_ip, username=username, password=password, look_for_keys=False, allow_agent=False)
        if ssh_connection:
            stdin, stdout, stderr = ssh_connection.exec_command('echo "testing"')
            return False if stderr.readlines() else True
        else:
            raise Exception('SSH connection failed for the device ' + device_name)
    else:
        raise Exception('Device {} not managed in the inventory. Status: {}'.format(device_name, device_status))

        return tmshell + tmsh_commands + ['save sys config'] +  add_sync_command(device_row[0].version, device_row[0].sync_failover_group_name) + ['quit']
    elif action == 'IMPLEMENT':
        return tmshell + tmsh_commands + ['save sys config'] + add_sync_command(device_row[0].version, device_row[0].sync_failover_group_name) + ['quit'], csv_final_dict
    else:
        return tmshell + tmsh_commands + ['quit']
